Univariate Analysis

What is the structure of your dataset?

There are 113937 observations in the Loan dataset with 81 features. I have subsetted the data and taken only 24 variables for analysis

What is/are the main feature(s) of interest in your dataset?

After reviewing the long list of variables, and thinking of all of the different paths of investigation, Ive decided to narrow my focus of investigation around deliquencies and their correlations

The main features for this exploration are: - Term: The length of the loan expressed in months - Loan Status: Current Status of the Loan - Cancelled - Charged off - Completed - Defaulted - FinalPaymentInProgress - Past Due

  • Borrower State: The two letter abbreviation of the state of the address of the borrower at the time the Listing was created.

  • Listing Category: The category of the listing that the borrower selected when posting their listing 0 - Not Available 1 - Debt Consolidation 2 - Home Improvement 3 - Business 4 - Personal Loan 5 - Student Use 6 - Auto 7- Other 8 - Baby&Adoption 9 - Boat 10 - Cosmetic Procedure 11 - Engagement Ring 12 - Green Loans 13 - Household Expenses 14 - Large Purchases 15 - Medical/Dental 16 - Motorcycle 17 - RV 18 - Taxes 19 - Vacation 20 - Wedding Loans

  • Credit Score Range Lower: The lower value representing the range of the borrowers credit score as provided by a consumer credit rating agency
  • Credit Score Range Upper: The upper value representing the range of the borrowers credit score as provided by a consumer credit rating agency
  • Bankcard Utilization: The percentage of available revolving credit that is utilized at the time the credit profile was pulled
  • Income Range: The income range of the borrower at the time the listing was created
  • Loan Original Amount: The origination amount of the loan

  • Investors: The number of investors that funded the loan

What other features in the dataset do you think will help support your
investigation into your feature(s) of interest?

These features help to contribute to deeper dives and identification of possible trends: - Listing Creation Date: The date the listing was created - Occupation: The Occupation selected by the Borrower at the time they created the listing - IsBorrowerHomeOwner: A Borrower will be classified as a homowner if they have a mortgage on their credit profile or provide documentation confirming they are a homeowner - BorrowerAPR: The Borrowers Annual Percentage Rate (APR) for the loan - BorrowerRate: The Borrowers interest rate for this loan - Recommendations: Number of recommendations the borrower had at the time the listing was created - TotalProsperLoans: Number of Prosper loans the borrower at the time they created this listing. This value will be null if the borrower had no prior loans - DebttoIncomeRatio: The debt to income ratio of the borrower at the time the credit profile was pulled - StatedMonthlyIncome: The monthly income the borrower stated at the time the listing was created

Did you create any new variables from existing variables in the dataset?

Yes,I have created three new variables: - Listing Category from Listing Category Numeric - LoanOriginatedYear from LoanOriginatedDate - Delinquent Borrowers from Loan Status

Of the features you investigated, were there any unusual distributions?
Did you perform any operations on the data to tidy, adjust, or change the form
of the data? If so, why did you do this?

I have performed data type conversions on date columns in the data to apply date functions such as extracting days, months or years on the data

Yes, I have created a Logistic Regression Model.The Borrower Rate and Investors has hig impact on Delinquency . For a unit change in Borrower rate , the percent of delinquency increases by a factor of 6.7, similary for a unit increase in Number of Investors, the delinquency increases by a factor of 6.9 respectively Credit Score, Loan Amount has a negative impact on Delinquency. Reflection

The Prosper Loan data set contains information on almost 113 thousand Loan accounts across 81 variables from around 2007. I started by understanding the individual variables in the data set, and then I explored interesting questions and leads as I continued to make observations on plots. Eventually, I explored the Delinquent Borrowers across many variables and created a logistic model to predict Delinquencies.

There was a clear trend between the Borrower Rate and Credit Score Range and delinquent borrowers. I was surprised that Bankcard Utilization did not have a strong positive correlation with Delinquent Borrowers. I struggled in selecting teh 21 variables from 81 variables, I need to deeply study loan terms in order to select main features and supporting features as well.

From the logistic model , i have learnt Borrower Rate and Investors have Strong Positive Correlation with Delinquent Borrowers which made my Investigation simpler and more focused.Similarly Credit Score and Loan Amount had negative relation on delinquency which is quite interesting .From my final plots , I could be able to say that for the credit score around 500 and Loan Amount less than 5000 , there are more delinquent Borrowers .Also Borrower Interest rate greater than 0.25 and Investors greater than 20 have more probability of delinquencies
